Package: abseqr
Title: Antibody and Nanobody Sequence Analysis Tools
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Sila Zeynep", "Akyuz", 
           email = "slazeynepakyuz@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: A toolkit for parsing, summarising, and visualising antibody and 
    nanobody sequences. Provides functions for reading FASTA files into tidy 
    data frames, extracting and analysing CDR3 regions, computing amino acid 
    composition, and producing publication-ready plots. Designed for 
    reproducible antibody sequence analysis workflows.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
Imports:
    dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    scales,
    stringr,
    tibble,
    tidyr,
    rlang
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    ggseqlogo
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
URL: https://github.com/slzynp/abseqr, https://slzynp.github.io/abseqr/
BugReports: https://github.com/slzynp/abseqr/issues
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
